@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Accumulus" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Accumulus is played on an 8 by 10 spaces game board. At the start
of a game, 14 tiles of 5 different types are placed on the bottom
of the board.

  Each time you click on a tile, it will disappear. If there are
tiles that are located above it, they will fall down towards the
empty space where the clicked tile was located.

  When tiles fall, the game checks if there are tiles of the same
type that are next to each of the fallen tiles, if there aren't,
you get points according to the number of fallen tiles that have
neighbouring tiles. That is: 1 tile = 1 point, 2 tiles = 2 points,
3 tiles = 4 points and so on, up to 9 tiles that give 256 points.
If at least one tile fell and it had no neighbouring tile of the
same type, then, ONE new tile will appear somewhere on the game
board.

  However, TWO additional tiles are added on the game board, when
either there are no tiles above a clicked tile, or the fallen tiles
have any same type tiles beside them. When there are two or more
tiles of the same type next to each other, these tiles will flash.

  Continue the game until the game board fills-up completely, then
the game will be over.

  Have fun!

@endnode

